    {
      "id": 13,
      "change_id": "3e0545f7-8fad-43b7-b975-c0a4e273b386",
      "node_type": "goal",
      "title": "Phase 12.1: Refactor XrpcMethodRegistry DI cleanup",
      "description": null,
      "status": "pending",
      "created_at": "2026-02-17T01:51:06.378460-05:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-17T01:51:06.378460-05:00",
      "metadata_json": "{\"branch\":\"main\",\"confidence\":85,\"prompt\":\"# Detailed Next Steps Plan\\n\\n## Phase 12: Architecture Refinement (Priority: High)\\n\\n### 12.1. Dependency Injection Cleanup (`XrpcMethodRegistry`)\\nThe `XrpcMethodRegistry` currently accepts `PDSApplication` but still extracts `legacyController` to pass to helper functions. This enforces a dependency on the legacy controller.\\n\\n- [ ] **Refactor `registerServerAccountAndSessionMethods`**\\n  - Change signature to accept `PDSAccountService` and `PDSConfiguration` directly instead of `PDSController`.\\n  - Update implementations to use extraction logic from services.\\n- [ ] **Refactor `extractDIDFromAuthHeader`**\\n  - Currently takes `PDSController` to access `serverHost` or `jwtMinter`.\\n  - Update to accept `PDSConfiguration` or `JWTMinter` directly.\\n- [ ] **Remove `application.legacyController` usage**\\n  - Identify all call sites in `registerMethodsWithDispatcher:application:`.\\n  - Replace with specific service properties from `PDSApplication` (e.g., `adminController`, `repoService`).\\n\\ngo\"}"
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "change_id": "ce302e89-0c06-4942-977c-4ef8df3f3164",
      "node_type": "goal",
      "title": "Production readiness: fix C1-C3, H1-H5, M1-M3 for small self-hoster",
      "description": null,
      "status": "pending",
      "created_at": "2026-02-17T18:13:31.838354-05:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-17T18:13:31.838354-05:00",
      "metadata_json": "{\"branch\":\"main\",\"confidence\":95,\"prompt\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Production Readiness Review — ATProtoPDS (Small Self-Hoster)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nProduction readiness assessment and remediation plan for self-hosting the Objective-C ATProtoPDS implementation. The codebase is substantially complete (96/96 core AT Protocol methods, OAuth/DPoP, SQLite persistence, logging) but has several gaps. Scope: **single-machine small self-hoster**, not distributed deployment.\\n\\n[Full plan omitted for brevity — see conversation transcript]\\n\\nFixes implemented:\\nC1: Wire Resend email provider into PDSApplication.m\\nC2: Enforce JWT issuer at startup (exit(1) if production + pds.local)\\nC3: Reverse proxy / HTTPS deployment documentation\\nH1: Content-Type header (was already present)\\nH2: Parse Resend error JSON body (name/message fields)\\nH3: Persist token invalidation to file (survives restarts)\\nH4: Warn on plain-text admin password at startup\\nH5: Warn on X-Admin-Token in production at startup\\nM1: Add 409 to retryable HTTP status codes\\nM2: Register NSUncaughtExceptionHandler (C function, not block)\\nM3: Apply WAL + performance PRAGMAs to service DB pools\"}"
    },
